fields.descriptive_line: Panel of 60 glazed tiles, possibly fritware with cuerda seca decoration depicting birds and vase of flowers against yellow ground, from the (demolished) south gate of the Topmaidan in Tehran, Qajar Iran, 1800-1825
fields.physical_description: Panel of 60 glazed tiles, possibly fritware with cuerda seca decoration depicting birds and vase of flowers against yellow ground, from the (demolished) south gate of the Topmaidan in Tehran, Qajar Iran, 1800-1825
fields.materials_techniques: Possibly fritware, but ceramic body is reddish and covered with white slip.
fields.history_note: From the south gate of the Tope Maidan at Teheran, recently destroyed.
